net.proteusframework.cms.controller

Class HTMLPageGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.cms.component.generator.GeneratorImpl<Page>
      • net.proteusframework.cms.controller.HTMLPageGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cacheable<Page>, Generator<Page>, Renderer<Page>

    @Configurable
public class HTMLPageGenerator
extends GeneratorImpl<Page>
    Simple generator that returns content that is HTML. This generator is specifically written to work with the HTML ContentElement.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

    • Method Detail

      • getDataSourceTimestamp

        public long getDataSourceTimestamp(CmsRequest<Page> request)
        Description copied from class: GeneratorImpl
        Get the latest timestamp of the data being used to generate the content. The timestamp should be for the content being generated by the generator. The timestamp should not represent data from other elements in the process chain with the exception of delegates not processed by CMS. This method is guaranteed to be called for every CMS (http / servlet) request.

        Returns the last modified time of the PageElement.

        Specified by:
        getDataSourceTimestamp in interface Generator<Page>
        Overrides:
        getDataSourceTimestamp in class GeneratorImpl<Page>
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the timestamp or -1 if unknown.

      • getIdentity

        public String getIdentity(CmsRequest<Page> request)
        Description copied from class: GeneratorImpl
        Return a string that uniquely identifies the information needed to generate or influence the content for the response.

        For example, if the response is dependent on a record from the database, an implementor should return a String representing the database key and a timestamp for when the record was last updated.

        Returns the last modified time of the PageElement.

        Specified by:
        getIdentity in interface Cacheable<Page>
        Overrides:
        getIdentity in class GeneratorImpl<Page>
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the identity of the generated content or null if unknown / unimplemented.

        The NDEs should be assembled in the preRenderProcess method. See the class level javadoc for order of method calls. The ProcessChain will gather the NDEs of any Renderers or PageElements that are delegated to.
